Managing Director of Kaduna Markets Development and Management Company, Hafiz Bayero, was on Monday evening involved in an accident along the Kaduna-Abuja highway. Bayero was said to be with his driver while returning from a trip to Abuja when the incident occured. Details surrounding the accident were still sketchy at the time of filing this report but Bayero was seen being rescued from the car with registration number 12E-04KD by sympathisers in a picture on social media. Though the State is yet to issue official statement on the incident, the Facebook page of Kaduna Market Development Company confirmed Bayero had an accident. The company posted on Facebook:  “Our Managing director, Hafiz Bayero actually had an accident with his driver today. But he is stable and gradually recovering. “We pray that the Almighty grant him rapid recovery. We appreciate your prayers.” 